Description: My client is looking for API DeveloperRole: API DeveloperLocation: Phoenix, AZDuration: 6+ MonthsStart Date: 05/02/2016Minimum Education Level: Bachelor's DegreePosition Description:Position Summary:Client is seeking an API Developer.  This position is responsible for the development, packaging and support of Application Programming Interfaces and supporting Class Libraries to be used by the software development teams within the organization.  The API Developer implements the model that conforms to the contextual domain architecture and governance needs of the organization. This position constructs software libraries at the enterprise level to meet the needs of the Administrative Office of the Courts (AOC).  The position performs pragmatic and innovative solutions for use in multiple projects following the detailed design decisions of the Chief Architect.This position provides development, support and problem resolution directly associated with the projects assigned.  In addition, this position participates in reviews of design specifications to adapt technical solutions to the AOC defined methodologies; participates and coordinates with other programmers and development teams to create efficient applications delivered within the constraints of a project plan; uses and employs best practices in technical solutions with enterprise domain objects as a focus.  This position also creates and maintains code level technical documentation for developed and supported application components and supporting utilities; and works consistently within the established AOC-ITD procedures for problem, project, and change management processes.  In addition, this position must interface and coordinate with internal/external agencies to ensure AOC-ITD standardization.Primary Duties:Identification, definition, packaging and support of WCF services and supporting Domain Libraries to be used by the software development teams.  Constructs software libraries at the enterprise level of use in multiple projects.  Provides development, support and problem resolution; reviews of design specifications to adapt technical solutions; participates and coordinates with other programmers and development teams; creates and maintains code level technical documentation; interface and coordinate with internal/external agencies.MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS:Bachelor's degree in a related field and at least five years' experience programming, analysis, design, development, implementation, quality assurance and applications support.  Directly related experience may substitute for the degree requirement.  A thorough understanding and familiarity with REST, and Web API development using the .Net platform with VB.Net, C#, JSON and XML is required.  This individual must be familiar with software development lifecycle methodologies (preferably CMMI); be experienced using source control and change management procedures; have a solid understanding of object oriented design concepts, separation of concerns, dependency injection; and a working technical knowledge of automated software development support tools.  In addition, this individual should have significant experience with business to business integration using SOAP and REST, OWIN, JWT and OpenID Connect.  The candidate will have knowledge of Domain Driven Development, Service and Resource Oriented Architectures, messaging strategies, event stores and an enterprise message queue.  The preferred candidate will have five years' experience programming and producing enterprise level, service oriented distributed applications.Please send your updated resume.Thanks & Regards,Anil Advent Global Solutions,Inc. E-mail: anil@adventglobal.comDirect: (281) 640 8940www.adventglobal.com

Description: Client Job Description The primary role of this position is to provide data analysis support to ITPM development project teams.  This position will analyze business requirements to identify and document all data needs, definitions around all data elements and all business rules associate with any data element.  This position will help to identify data redundancies, where appropriate provide options to reduce data redundancy.  This position will be responsible for the creation of a data dictionary for each project he/she assigned to. This position will be responsible for developing data flow diagrams and logical data models. This position will assist with the identification of information flow, content issues and the transformation of business requirements into logical data and system models.  This position is eligible for telework and/or a flexible work schedule. Up to 2 days telework can be considered.  This position is not eligible for over-time and will be capped at 40 hours a week.What knowledge, skills, abilities, experiences, certifications are needed for this position?  Data Modeling and Database Design (strong knowledge of relational database concepts)  SQL (PL/SQL is a plus) Data Integration Practices Strong analytical skills, attention to detail and logical thinking Ability to understand the business data needs and translate into data models (DFDs, DSDs and/or ERDs) Ability to create ETL specifications and develop data mappings Ability to engage in detailed analysis of data discrepancies to determine the source and resolution of errors Clear and concise documentation skills High level knowledge of programming practices Aptitude for learning new technologies/applications/businesses Excellent presentation, communication and customer service skills while maintaining a professional manner Self-motivated team player able to work cooperatively in a team environment Ability to work under pressure, prioritize and meet deadlines when required Remain flexible on changing workloads and priorities Ability to communicate with diversified stakeholders Data Warehousing is a plus Business Intelligence is a plus ITIL certification is a plus Industry specific knowledge regarding asset inventory systems is a plus Industry specific knowledge regarding service portfolio management systems is a plusEssential Skills/Competencies: 5+ years of data requirements gathering experience  5+ years of logical Data Modeling  5+ years of experience in data-centric positions or roles 3+ years of SQL (PL/SQL is a plus) Hands-on experience with ETL Tools is a plus Public Sector background/experience is a plus *Experience with Microsoft Dynamics CRM and/or RSA Archer a plus

Description: Currently, we are recruiting for a true Data Analytics Specialist  The Data Analytics Team (part of the EIS Department) is dedicated to improving healthcare through strategic and technology-based transformation. This team will interface with customers throughout the medical center, executive leadership, various committees and be involved in performance improvement initiatives. This team will assist in the transformation of data as the healthcare industry moves from a volume based business to a value based business. Summary of Essential Job Duties: Â   This position is responsible for serving as a Subject Matter Expert/ Epic application expert / Data Analytics Specialist. Primary Responsibilities  - Customer service and management  o Intake of data requests and understanding of business need.  o Establish trusting professional relationships with all customers.  o Maintain alignment of expectations , timelines and priorities  o Ensure communication and status updates of request from initiation to completion  - Analysis and critical thinking  o By applying knowledge of data analysis, applicable Epic applications, critical-thinking skills, and healthcare experience/expertise perform research and analysis of business request/issues.  o Recommend intelligent solutions to solve problems and address business challenges. If necessary, those that don't necessarily align with initial customer request  - Requirements and documentation  o Work closely with the applications teams and/or subject matter experts to understand workflow, documentation standards and especially potential gaps  o Gather clear and concise requirements, interpret the finding and translate the information, as needed, into documented business specifications for the report development  - Design  o Work closely with technical teams ( Clarity, EDW and other report developers) to ensure understanding of data models and potential design of output  o Structure analytical results in an organized, visual manner - demonstrate knowledge of the various tools that can be applied and developed to present the data to the requestor  - Testing and validation  o Perform data scrubbing, trouble-shooting, quality checking, and usability analysis to identify anomalies, which need to be addressed prior to delivery of results.  o Facilitate user acceptance testing, including partnering with reporting customers to guide them through report review and approval.  The position provides an exciting opportunity to work with our leadership team to make a substantive impact in the healthcare environment especially in the analytics and data transformation arena! Experience: Â   - 5+ years of Healthcare requirements gathering, analysis, design and implementation experience in either the clinical or financial arena  - Experience in data mining, statistical analysis, and data transformation/manipulation.  - Advanced analytic skills with the ability to analyze and interpret data through complex analysis.  - Experience with patient care-oriented databases, hospital-based administrative database applications and data warehousing technology preferred.  - Knowledge of HIPAA compliance and security requirements as it relates to healthcare data. Other applicable data sets include Census, Eligibility, and Membership data sets.  - Experience in defining business process flows and work flows  -Experience working with large data repositories and/or relational databases.  -Expertise in MS Excel, with proficiency using formulas, PivotTables, linked worksheets, graphing and other reporting and presentation features.  -Ability to work on multiple projects simultaneously with minimal supervision.  -Strong knowledge of project management methodologies and experience managing multiple projects  -Ability to quickly adapt to changes in both technology and business environments.  -Detail oriented and ability to analyze data, and apply investigative skills in resolving issues.  -Ability to produce clear, written operational instructions and supporting documentation.  -Ability to troubleshoot technical and functional problems.  -Exceptional written and oral communication skills.  -Highly self-motivated and directed with keen attention to detail; Ability to work independently with minimal supervision and manage multiple priorities  Computer Skills  - Advanced Visio  - Strong computer skills including Windows, Exchange/Outlook, Word, Excel, Visio, PowerPoint and Project  - Epic application level knowledge / certification  - And other business productivity tools

Position: Public Health M & E Data Analyst
Description: Description:The Federal Health Operation is seeking a full time Public Health Program Monitoring and Evaluation Data Analyst to work with the Naval Health Research Center (NHRC)/Department of Defense (DoD) HIV/AIDS Prevention Program (DHAPP) in San Diego, CA. This individual will support the Strategic Information Team. The purpose of this position is to strengthen the collection, management, and use of strategic information in order to monitor and improve programs supported by DHAPP. This includes providing in-person and virtual technical assistance to DHAPP partners (DHAPP field offices and partner militaries) in monitoring and evaluation (M&E), in program quality monitoring, and in the effective use of strategic information for planning and programmatic decision making, and developing M&E and other data related strategies for HIV/AIDS programs. International and domestic travel is a part of this position. The candidate will collect, organize, verify, and manage routinely reported data received from DHAPP field programs. Assist staff to analyze, interpret, and apply existing epidemiological, programmatic, and other relevant data to effectively plan future projects, allocate resources, and make informed programmatic decisions. Assist staff with understanding and applying M&E data while focusing on quality improvement of services and improving the accuracy of reported program data. This individual will work with foreign country partner programs to guide strategic information investments in order to improve the quality of delivered services. Participate in the evaluation and assessment of DHAPP programs and activities. Assist with training staff on how to best use program data, assess and improve data quality, use data management and analysis tools, and realistically set program targets. Support staff with understanding and using the Site Improvement Monitoring System (SIMS) data and the analysis of this data in order to improve program quality. The incumbent will respond to routine and ad hoc requests for information and other data reporting. Manage these data correspondence and project communications. Assist with data management and reporting requirements for SIMS site-level data. Participate in PEPFAR working groups such as those related to quality assurance, program quality improvement, monitoring and evaluation, and the Interagency Collaborative for Program Improvement. Qualifications:Qualifications: 1. Education: Minimum of a master?s degree in a relevant technical field (e.g. public health, epidemiology, quality assurance, or related field) from an accredited college or university. 2. Prior Work Experience: Minimum of two years of experience in public health M&E, international health, health science, or in HIV/STI programs. Prior work experience with a USG Agency, military, or other international/local organization is advantageous. Experience using statistical software such as SAS or SPSS is desirable. Experience with GIS software is also desirable. Experience with Microsoft Office products such as Word, Excel, and Outlook is expected. Data management and analysis using Excel or Access is beneficial. 3. Language Proficiency: Written and oral proficiency in English is required. The incumbent is required to be capable of preparing documents such as technical and progress reports. Reports, correspondences, and documents are to be prepared in a professional and competent manner requiring little or no editorial changes. The ability to communicate information effectively with public health scientists and program staff is required. 4. Knowledge: Knowledge of concepts, principles, techniques and practices of monitoring and/or evaluation, and data quality assessment is required. Knowledge of concepts, principles, techniques and practices of HIV/AIDS prevention, care, treatment, and support programs is desirable. An understanding and knowledge of USG regulations and procedures is beneficial. 5. Travel: The incumbent must be willing and able to travel domestically and internationally. This position is expected to require travel up to 25%. 6. Citizenship: Due to Federal contract regulations, US citizenship (no dual US citizenship) and the ability to obtain a Secret Clearance is required. 7. Other: The incumbent should have an interest in working with and on behalf of militaries. An ability to interact positively and professionally within an academic/evidence based environment and have excellent critical thinking and problem-solving skills. The candidate must be able to work both independently and cooperatively in an established culturally diverse team setting. The individual will be required to manage multiple tasks simultaneously and be flexible in responding to changing demands, timelines, and priorities. The incumbent must be able and willing to work early and late hours and additional hours beyond the established 40 hour work week as sometimes necessary. Supervision Received: The Public Health Program Monitoring and Evaluation Data Analyst will work under the direction of the Strategic Information Team Leader, the NHRC/DHAPP management team, and Leidos management. The incumbent will work with a great deal of independence. S/he will establish priorities, adhere to and meet established deadlines, and perform responsibilities and duties with minimal guidance and follow up. Leidos Overview:Leidos is an applied solutions company focused on markets that are seeing converging business and technological trends, and address basic, enduring human needs: defense and national security, health and life sciences, and energy, engineering and infrastructure. The Company's approximately 20,000 employees serve customers in the U.S. Department of Defense, the intelligence community, the U.S. Department of Homeland Security, other U.S. Government civil agencies and commercial health and engineering markets.  Qualified women, minorities, individuals with disabilities and protected veterans are encouraged to apply.     Leidos is an Equal Opportunity Employer.

Description: Microsoft SQL Server Database Developer Â  Job Description: The candidate will take the lead role in researching, identifying, and documenting the data sources and data fields that populate or will populate surgery-related data in a Corporate Data Warehouse (CDW) and develop a Microsoft SQL Server 2012 database with the data points the customer needs to assess, identify, and monitor the surgery-related data. Tasks associated with this SOW include the creation of a Microsoft SQL Server 2012 data structure for storage, updates, change logs, and metadata for surgery-related data in the CDW as well as the design, configuration, testing, and deployment of SQL stored procedures for data retrieval and identification of records that changed. The customer also requires cross-validation of data between new surgery-related tables and existing CDW tables to identify any missing or inconsistent records. In addition, the candidate will design, configure, and publish a patient-specific report for surgery patients that show specialty care timelines in graphical and tabular form. Finally, the candidate will transition training back to the customer at project completion including all relevant documentation of schema and data sources utilized. The candidate will work collaboratively with the customer statistical and program analyst teams to complete the tasks in a collaborative on-site environment in Denver, Colorado. The candidate will have full access to the project team and subject matter experts. Â  Job Responsibilities/Qualifications:  The ideal candidate should possess 3 or more years of related experience described in the Job Description. The candidate will provide a detailed work plan and briefing for the project team, which presents the contractor's plan for completing the task order. The candidate will create a Microsoft SQL Server 2012 data structure for storage, updates, change logs, and metadata for surgery-related data in the CDW (inclusive of linked data from existing production domains such as encounters, admissions, vital status). The candidate will provide cross-validation of data between new surgery tables and existing CDW tables to identify any missing or inconsistent records. The candidate will complete the design, configuration, testing, and deployment of SQL stored procedures for data retrieval, identification of records that changed, and summary information, e.g., case counts, percent of fields containing missing data, sites with no changes. The candidate shall complete nightly refresh of the SQL Server data tables for surgery-related data. The candidate will complete the configuration and design of reports that use these SQL tables (SQL Server Reporting Services), including user subscriptions and notifications as well as drill-down and drill-through functionality. The candidate will develop a report that uses natural language processing of free text fields to identify records of interest (e.g. searching for signs of infection in clinic notes, evidence of planned readmission) stored as text integration utility (TIU) documents in the CDW. The candidate will provide transition training back to the customer at project completion including all relevant documentation of schema and data sources utilized. The candidate will develop a patient-specific report for surgery patients showing specialty care timelines in graphical and tabular form. The patient-specific report shall include timelines between the following events: primary care visit to specialty care consult clinic visit, surgery clinic visit to surgery request, surgery request to actual operating room case or cancellation/rescheduling, recorded postoperative events including readmission, etc.   Technical Expertise. The candidate should have: Work history of Microsoft SQL Server database design, maintenance, and content/structure updates Work history of SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS) Knowledge of VHA data structures (VistA, BMS, Lab, DSS) and the use of VA FileMan to extract local VistA data; VSSC aggregation/reports of VHA data Also desirable but not required is knowledge and application of Pyramid Analytics software for data mining, analytics, and reporting (dashboards)    Bachelors Degree in a related technical discipline, or the equivalent combination of education, technical training or work experience. All candidates will demonstrate strong independent problem solving, troubleshooting, analytical and conceptual skills Able to manage multiple tasks and meet scheduled dates. The candidate must be able to adapt in a rapid changing environment, a fast learner and self-starter. Excellent written and communication skills and can work independently and well within groups. Description: Opportunity Alert! Homes.com is looking for a Database Administrator (DBA) to join a growing team of IT professionals working to support our premier Internet real estate portal. This individual will participate in exercises surrounding database operations, maintenance, availability, and performance in a 24x7 production environment. DBAs at Homes.com are focused on innovation for our online business services, while ensuring that all database software systems and related procedures adhere to organizational values.| Join Us. Achieve. Be Recognized.  Your Opportunity  * Responsible for the day-to-day operations, maintenance, availability and performance of the all production databases in a 24x7 production environment  * Configure and support the SQL/NoSQL server databases  * Perform problem resolution and root cause analysis on database issues  * Performance tuning, monitoring and troubleshooting database servers  * Capacity planning and backup/recovery activities  * Maintain data warehouse reports and rollups  * Maintain and oversee production SQL database environment including performance tuning, backup, recovery, and disaster  * Write complex stored procedures and functions per requirements  * Manage the lifecycle of MongoDB databases including database sizing, deployment automation, monitoring and tuning  * Perform document modeling, querying, indexing and tuning for both our MongoDB and Solr environments  * Implement MongoDB high availability concepts such as sharding and replication Requirements  Contribute Your Knowledge, Skills and Abilities  * In-depth T-SQL and SQL Server management experience  * Advanced knowledge of debugging and troubleshooting databases  * Operational experience with MongoDB  * Experience with moving data and objects from Oracle to SQL Server a plus  * Experience working in a team environment  * Bachelors or Masters in Computer Science or related degree or equivalent job experience About Homes.com: Â   Homes.com is a part of Homes Media Solutions, which is a division of Dominion Enterprises, and a leading provider of real estate advertising solutions. For over 15 years we have offered many products that facilitate brand advertising, listing exposure and lead generation to agents, brokers, and builders. About Dominion Enterprises: Â   Dominion Enterprises is a leading online marketing and software services company offering client solutions across multiple targeted business verticals. Our iconic B2C web and mobile portals, including ForRent.com, Homes.com, CycleTrader.com and BoatTrader.com, generate nearly 30 million unique visits monthly. Our B2B cloud SaaS solutions directly support clients in establishing their online and mobile brands, generating leads, and managing customer relationships. We have more than 40 businesses and 3,000 employees in our Norfolk, Va. home office, across the U.S., and internationally. See our complete story at www.dominionenterprises.com. We offer a dynamic environment, excellent growth opportunities, competitive earnings and a comprehensive benefits package that includes a generous 401(k). Dominion Enterprises is an equal opportunity employer and supports a diverse workforce. Dominion is a drug-testing employer.
Skills: Analysis, B2B, B2C, Capacity Planning, Database, Data Warehouse, DBA, Lifecycle, Management, Modeling, MongoDB, NoSQL, Oracle, Solr, SQL, SQL Server, Testing

4 years of professional experience in developing business requirements, functional specifications, user interface specifications and documenting process flows* 2 - 4 years of experience working in one or more of the following roles is highly desirable: Quality Assurance analyst, System Analyst, or Data Analyst with SQL query skills* 2 - 4 years of experience working with the implementation of enterprise class solutions and data warehousing or Business Intelligence is highly desirable* Functional Specification Documentation* Business Requirements Gathering* Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC)* Project Management Lifecycle* Excellent written and oral communication skills* Knowledge of Database Concepts* Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Project, and Visio)* SQL/Query Tools required* Travel and Hospitality experience desired but not required* Must be self-motivated and able to work in a team environment with limited supervision* Ability to communicate effectively (written and verbal) and present a professional image* Ability to organize and conduct effective meetings* Ability and desire to learn new technologies and software feature usage, often in a self-starting mode* Must have a commitment to teamwork and customer service, and be able to perform well in a process-oriented, collaborative team environment* Must have strong diagnostic and analytical skills with attention to detail* Must be results oriented and have a track record of timely high-quality achievement of deliverables* Must be able to work effectively in a fast-pace, dynamic environmentKforce is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. Description: JOB FAMILY DESCRIPTION  Responsible for deploying the release of new technologies as well as the design, installation, configuration, maintenance and system integration testing performance of PC/server operating systems, related utilities and hardware. Ensure that the enterprise compliance policies are maintained and remediate any Hadoop vulnerabilities, lead the installation of new/expansion or upgrades, assist in debugging issues with the application teams, ensure system is performing optimally and recommend improvements, create/update diagrams and runbooks.  GENERAL DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES  * Responsible for implementation and ongoing administration of Hadoop infrastructure through the installation, maintenance and enhancements for hardware and software systems.  * Work with data delivery teams to setup new Hadoop users and control user access and passwords (i.e.; setting up Linux users, Kerberos principals, testing HDFS, Hive, Pig, MapReduce access, etc.)  * Proposes and implements systems enhancements that will improve the reliability and performance of the system. Performance tuning of Hadoop clusters and Hadoop MapReduce routines.  * Monitors usage and performance while screening Hadoop cluster job performance and capacity planning.  * Trains personnel on system usage.  * Troubleshoots server, software and hardware issues.  * Assists with recommending, scheduling and implementing system hardware and/or software upgrades or repairs.  * Researches, evaluates and recommends software and hardware products.  * Ensure compliance policies are maintained and remediate any Hadoop vulnerabilities while maintaining a secure systems environment.  * Provides new hardware specifications to users based on application needs and anticipated growth.  * Point of contact for vendor escalation  * Performs other duties as required.  EDUCATIONAL GUIDELINES  Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or the equivalent combination of education, training, or work experience. Description: The Network Data Engineers role is to design, build and optimize network hardware and software systems to provide efficient communications for data and voice applications over company networks. This includes the support and configuration of enterprise-class network platforms from Cisco Systems to include routing and switching platforms, wireless network components, WAN optimization platforms and network security devices. Responsibilities of this role will also include implementing and supporting optimized and efficient communications mechanisms that provide priority for critical business systems applications and utilize congestion avoidance techniques over redundant network paths. Network management and monitoring applications will be installed, configured and utilized to ensure efficient network operations, provide capacity planning and verify the status of network devices to ensure maximum network availability. The role will be tasked with providing support for company voice and data networks and the resolution of trouble tickets initiated by the help desk, end users and those escalated from team members. Description: The Data Scientist family is accountable for using data to make decisions, which includes building predictive models and developing new machine learning techniques that enable our client to make better decisions to achieve its goals. The Data Scientist Family requires Analytic Agility, the ability to quickly learn new modeling/machine learning techniques, programming languages, and see how these ideas can integrate to optimize the business.  This role is responsible for leading the use of data to make decisions. This includes the development and management of new machine learning predictive modeling algorithms; the coding development of tools that use machine learning/predictive modeling to make business decisions; searching for and integrating new data (both internal and external) that improves our modeling and machine learning results (and ultimately our decisions); and discovery of solutions to business problems that can be solved through the use of machine learning/predictive modeling. This role will also begin to manage projects of medium to high complexity.  * Uses best practices to develop statistical, machine learning techniques to build models on telematics data that would handle a wide range of problems ranging from probabilistic inference on phone trajectories, data fusion between noisy sensors, and classification of driving behavior.  * Work on data analysis and predictive modeling of sensor data collected from the car and mobile phones (GPS, accelerometer, gyroscope, etc.)  * Identify KPI's generated from telematics sensor data.  * Manages data and data requests to improve the accuracy of our data and decisions made from data analysis.  * Uses and learns a wide variety of tools and languages to achieve results (e.g., R, Python, Hadoop).  * Identifies languages and tools that can bring efficiencies or needed techniques to the team.  * Works on data and business problems to drive improved business results through designing, building, and partnering to implement models.  * Collaborates the with team in order to improve the effectiveness of business decisions through the use of data and machine learning/predictive modeling.  * Understands the business' problems to identify the optimal modeling approach.  * Communicates to team members, leadership and stakeholders on findings to ensure models are well understood and incorporated into business processes.  * Utilizes effective project planning techniques to break down moderately complex projects into tasks and ensure deadlines are kept.  * Works with leaders to ensure the project will meet their needs.  * The development and execution of a communication strategy, with appropriate coaching, that keeps all relevant stakeholders informed and provides an opportunity to influence the direction of the work.  Job Qualifications  Degree in a quantitative field such as statistics, mathematics, computer science, finance.  * Master's or PhD preferred in a quantitative field such as statistics, mathematics, computer science, finance, or economics.  * Experience in using statistical modeling and/or machine learning techniques to build models on telematics / sensor data to drive company's business results.  * Strong understanding of telematics and mobile phone sensors.  * Experience in managing and manipulating large, complex datasets.  * Experience in working with statistical software such as SAS, SPSS, MatLab, R, CART, etc.  * Understanding of the Insurance market place; economics and regulation preferred.  * Ability to code and develop prototypes in languages such as Python, Perl, Java, C.  * Knowledge of advanced modeling technique.  * Ability to analyze and interpret moderate to complex concepts.  * Ability to provide written and oral interpretation of highly specialized terms and data, and ability to present this data to others with different levels of expertise.  * Demonstrated analytic agility.  #dj  All qualified candidates are encouraged to apply by submitting their resume as an MS word document including a cover letter with a summary of relevant qualifications, highlighting clearly any special or relevant experience.
Skills: Algorithms, Analysis, Data Analysis, Development, GPS, Hadoop, Java, Management, Matlab, Modeling, Perl, Programming, Project, Python, SAS

Description: The main task of the group is to use state of the art Machine Learning methods in order to generate financial forecasts from large datasets. As such, the role involves developing novel machine learning techniques and applying them to seek patterns in large, dirty and noisy data sets. A firm understanding of the underlying mathematics will be needed to adapt modelling techniques to fit the problem space. The resulting codebase will be at the forefront of machine learning and pushing its boundaries into new and exciting areas. A prerequisite is an extremely strong background in mathematics and computer science. A post-graduate degree in machine learning is desirable. The successful candidates should be able to understand the theoretical justifications for the machine learning techniques as well as be able to create the software to apply the techniques, and where necessary develop those techniques into new areas.The successful candidate will be someone who is not just a user of machine learning libraries, but understands and can successfully use a number of approaches, e.g.: classification, clustering, linear models. Knowledge and practical experience in application of Bayesian methods, Gaussian processes and approximate inference is required, any knowledge of kernel methods, hidden Markov models & linear dynamic systems would be a plus. What is essential is a hands-on ability to apply mathematical concepts to real world financial problems, to implement theoretical insights as working code, and the ability to work independently in a research environment. Numerical programming is an integral part of the role and experience in an object oriented language is very desirable.Educational background: - A PhD degree from one of the worlds leading universities or research labs in one of the following fields: Statistics, Applied Mathematics, Computer Science, Speech Recognition, Electrical/Electronic Engineering or Physics.- Up to date knowledge in the field of machine learning and statistical learning- Deep and thorough understanding of the theoretical justifications of ML techniques and methods.Additional skills that they are seeking include: - Ability to conduct the full spectrum of research on oneâ€™s own: from model design to algorithm development to testing.- Comfort with some scripting language (Python/Unix shell/etc.) and a numerical language (R/Matlab).- C++ / Perl / Bash knowledge is also ideal- Experience working with real world large datasets- Experience at top-tier research labs / ML conferences / publications- Awards and honours in leading mathematics / physics / computer science competitions
Skills: Machine Learning, Quant, Researcher, PhD, C++, Python

Description: Technical Lead Qualification: Bachelors in science , engineering or equivalentResponsibility:Requirement Understanding and Analysis: * Understand the functional/ nonfunctional requirements. * Participate in client calls and prepare the clarification list to seek clarifications. * Prepare the list of requirements and seek review inputs from the key stakeholders. * Update requirements traceability matrix. * Create impact analysis document (for simple change) to understand the impact on the existing functionality, as required. Design: * Provide inputs to create the low level design for the module based on the understanding of the requirement and HLD. * Identify the list of reusable assets that can be used and share inputs. * Share the list of components with the Senior Developer/ other relevant stakeholders and seek inputs. Coding: * Based on LLD , identify the component that needs to be created. * Set up the environment for creating the component. * Replicate the existing code to the environment. * Establish connection to the databases. * Conduct coding as per finalized technical specification document. * Follow coding standards and best practices to check code quality. * Generate code quality document for the code review through various tools (Informatica, Aqua). * Share the developed code for review. * Rework on the code based on inputs shared by the Sr Developer and Module Lead if required. * Identify unit test case scenarios based on the design. * Prepare unit test cases and test data under guidance. * Merge code in the build environment and seek inputs from the Senior Developer. * Conduct peer review for the other team members. * Conduct technical troubleshooting if required. Testing Management: * Conduct unit testing based on the identified test scenarios. * Fix simple defects identified during unit testing. * Prepare unit test document based on the test results and share the same for review. * Integrate and conduct system integration testing. * Address queries raised by QA team within defined timelines. * Analyze and fix the defects identified during functional / non functional testing. * Understand the impact/ criticality and priority of the defect. * Conduct regression testing for QA testing. * Report defect status as per project standard process within agreed timelines. * Track the status of defects using the test management tool (ALM, QC ). * Close the defect in test management tool once resolved. Configuration Management: * Branch off the existing code in the version control tool (VSS, CSV). * Identify configurable items. * Maintain version control across different configurable items (documents component, data mapping clarification document etc). Deployment: * Share the environment set up details with the deployment team. * Provide inputs on instructions (in case standard). * Create a deployment package under guidance of senior members in the team. * Raise deployment request to deployment team to deploy the code in the integrated environment. * Review the deployed component in the environment. * Load the test data. * Conduct smoke testing under guidance. * Share notification with QA team post completion of testing.Service Support and Maintenance: Specific to production and maintenance support: * Prioritize incidents based on criticality. * Route the defects logged to the right stakeholder if required. * Attend user calls, and capture required information and incident details for logging. * Coordinate with the different stakeholders to resolve as per SLA. * Run appropriate tests, once the defect is resolved. * Track the status in the test management tool (QC, Alma etc). * In case of any recurring incidents, prepare a learning document capturing the known errors. * Provide inputs to module lead in creation of transition plan (project steps and milestones). Knowledge Management: * Create specific artifacts for tasks allocated by Lead. * Share artifact with supervisor for review. * Upload article in the knowledge management repository. * Search the knowledge repository for information to resolve problems. * Apply best practices/ learning during the code development. * Create reusable assets and their documentation. * Create value addition documents (value added by team to the client) and share it with the team. People Management: * Provide inputs in creation of training courses and supporting artifacts on the training server such as demo, presentation. * Conduct training or knowledge sharing sessions (in case of niche technology).Qualifications: Technical Skills SNo Primary Skill Proficiency Level * Rqrd./Dsrd. 1 IBM Cognos Report Studio PL2 Required 2 Sql PL2 Desired 3 Oracle PL1 Desired 4 Unix Shell Scripting PL1 Desired 5 IBM Infosphere Datastage PL2 Required Domain Skills SNo Primary Skill Proficiency Level * Rqrd./Dsrd. 1 Customer & service excellence NA Required * Proficiency Legends Proficiency Level Generic Reference PL1 The associate has basic awareness and comprehension of the skill and is in the process of acquiring this skill through various channels. PL2 The associate possesses working knowledge of the skill, and can actively and independently apply this skill in engagements and projects. PL3 The associate has comprehensive, in-depth and specialized knowledge of the skill. She / he has extensively demonstrated successful application of the skill in engagements or projects. PL4 The associate can function as a subject matter expert for this skill. The associate is capable of analyzing, evaluating and synthesizing solutions using the skill. Description: Come be a Data Engineer with an expanding Silicon Valley company taking on London, where you will work with data scientists, designers, architects, and strategists in holistic teams, using your skills and knowledge to help our clients solve tough problems across the technology spectrum - including architecting, designing, creating, extending, and re-platforming their data platforms.   We facilitate our clients to treat their data as a strategic resource, and to use data to gain a competitive advantage in their industries. We have worked with clients in many sectors - including digital media, consumer web, financial services, and business analytics - and are rapidly expanding our client base with forward-thinking, fast-paced companies in the high tech, software, and retail industries. We pride ourselves in providing the best to our clients, we expect our solutions to stand on their own as if they were a product we sell. We go through the same process (continuous integration, quality assurance, stress testing, etc.) that any successful product company does.   You will have access to legacy and emerging vendors in data, as well as industry experts in the field, with whom our company has strong relationships. You will work with all of these parties to help us learn, discuss, and influence developments in the field.    Data engineering here encompasses a wide variety of data challenges. Each Data Engineer brings a unique and valuable skill set to the team, and we value a variety of perspectives when solving a problem. Because we want you to continue developing your skills and establishing your public reputation, and we care deeply about giving back to the data community, you will also have the opportunity to attend and present at conferences, contribute to the open source community, and create new generations of enterprise software.   Our TeamWe are a group of world-class data scientists, data engineers, platform architects, strategists, and consultants that have delivered complex solutions to some of the world's best-known brands. Not only are we approaching data-driven technology development in a new way, we also have an amazing team! By working with some of the brightest minds in data science and engineering, you will have the opportunity to both learn and contribute to solving challenging data problems at every phase.
Skills: Data Engineer

Description: Overview:The Extract Transform Load (ETL) Developer II is responsible in delivering the data strategy and the construction, delivery and maintenance approach of the ETL portion of the data architecture at Patterson Companies. The ETL Developer II will also provide a high level of ETL technical services and support to both internal and external clients; is considered an expert in multiple ETL technologies; maps data source to destination; has worked successfully integrating large vendor solutions and mentors others on ETL best practices and approaches within Patterson Companies' technical organization. Description: Senior SQL Server Database Administrator Position Description: Â   With offices spanning the globe, and employee tenure stretching into five decades, company offers exceptional opportunities to grow your career with a dedicated and supportive team of the industry's best people and the most rewarding challenges. From our focused, energetic work teams to our collaborative, results-oriented environment, company values its employees and wants them to know they're part of an industry global leader.  Work as an experienced DBA to support SQL Server and SQL Server applications. Provide support for Production and non-production (development, test, QA and Staging) databases.  The Sr. SQL DBA will also be responsible for providing critical SQL Server database support as well as for supplying technical direction and guidance to our junior resources. This role requires thorough understanding of complex database architectures (utilizing new features of SQL Server); several bolt on applications, strict change control process and proactive performance tuning.  Some of the primary responsibilities of this role would include owning, tracking and resolving database related incidents and requests, fulfilling requests and resolving incidents within SLAs, reviewing service related reports (e.g.: database backups, maintenance, monitoring) on a daily basis to ensure service related issues are identified and resolved within established SLAs, responding to database related alerts and escalations and working with database engineering to come up with strategic solutions to recurring problems.  The ideal Senior SQL Server Database Administrator is results-driven and understands the underlying needs of supporting our business and providing outstanding service to our customers. Responsibilities: Â   * Work closely with functional end users and development team to support implemented Microsoft Applications, Development Tools, and 3rd party solutions.  * Work with Systems DBA and infrastructure team to coordinate upgrades, patches and resolve any cross functional issues.  * Supports the development team for functional enhancements, trouble shooting and resolution.  * Plans and coordinates application/tools changes, installation of upgrades, patches and new versions, interacting with Systems DBA and Infrastructure teams.  * Provide on-call support.  * Mentor other DBAs in best practice and automation of tasks whenever and wherever possible.  * Willing to lead adoption of new technologies to improve team efficiency.  * Continually improve and automate standard SQL installations, and other tasks, for multiple environments through repeatable processes.  * Perform or coordinate database installs, upgrades, patching and implement infrastructure changes in accordance with IT configuration and change management policies.  * Ensure monitoring is in place in the database environment for availability, performance, and security.  * Perform complex data analysis or troubleshooting, and follow up with design, support, and documentation.  * Plan, drive and implement capacity, growth and best practice for the SQL Server architecture and prepare documentation for support.  * Knowledge of High Availability (HA) and Disaster Recovery (DR) options for MSSQL Server.  * Capacity planning, resource utilization analysis, performance tuning including enabling and interpreting SQL profiler and SQL tracing.  * Performs database installations, configuration, Patch Updates, monitoring, maintenance and version upgrades.  * Participates in conceptual, logical data modeling and physical design, database implementation, maintenance and support.  * SQL Database design, developing ET&L's with SSIS, manages database objects including writing stored procedures, tables, and views in support of new application enhancements and data interfaces including designing and implementation of Data Warehouses.  Position Requirements  * Worked on 24 x 7 Production Support or implementation both single node and clustered environments  * Worked in a SQL Server Clustered/HA Environment  * Worked with SQL Server Replication  * Extensive Patch Application experience  * Microsoft SQL Server DBA experience of over 5 - 10 years' experience

Description: Sr. Mongodb DBA/Architect Position Description: Â   The ideal candidate must demonstrate in-depth knowledge and understanding of MongoDB. This individual will be responsible for monitoring, maintaining existing databases, resolving complex database issues, optimizing performance, and implementing and documenting protocols for disaster recovery, configuration management, and security. They will also provide leadership, expertise and mentoring to other team members on best practices and advanced techniques. The DBA is part of a large heterogeneous environment and will be responsible for providing critical database analaysis, design, development and support as well guidance to application development teams. Responsible for defining, implementing, and maintaining database structures, procedures, and techniques to ensure data security and integrity. Expected to have a working understanding of DB standards and reasons for implementation, and is expected to understand Change Management methodology and its utilization for database changes. Requires  a service oriented mentality and a high sense of ownership of the problems and requests assigned.  Essential Duties and Responsibilities  - Skilled in backups & disaster recovery  - 24-7 production support experience  - Experience in performing Mongo DBA operational routines  - MMS configuration experience  - Configuring and monitoring replica sets  - Optimizing database/query performance  - Configuring Sharding , monitoring, and identify the proper shard key  - Strong Databases and Network problem solving and troubleshooting skills  - Advise customers on architectures, patterns, and strategies for making best use of MongoDB  - Understanding client requirements by participating in meetings. Able to Scope and estimate the work effort for each requirement.  - Report on business benefits for management and executives.  - Experience maintaining database performance by monitoring space, CPU usage, fragmentation of data, and by tuning queries, scheduling jobs, setting alerts, etc.  - Demonstrated ability to develop, communicate, and carry out procedures designed to facilitate recovery from database failure, such as online backups, archiving, and exports.  - Demonstrated ability to assist with on-going development of database change control and versioning procedures and work with data architects and developers to migrate database changes into test, user-acceptance and production environments.  Demonstrated ability to establish standards and policies to ensure enterprise information assets are properly secured and protected by appropriate access management and privacy controls. Position Requirements: Â   Minimum Education  - Bachelors Degree or Associate's degree specializing in information systems, technology, orequivalent work experience.  Minimum Experience  - 5+ years professional information technology experience in database administration working with Mongodb.  - 5+ years of hands on experience administering/monitoring high performance, high availability database clusters.  Additional Requirements  - Worked on 24 x 7 Production Support or implementation both single node and dual node environments  - Extensive Patch Application experience  - Worked on Backup & Recovery issues  - Good Performance tuning experience  - Excellent communication, interpersonal and organization skills  - Demonstrated ability to research and solve issues  - Demonstrated ability to deliver results in a high-energy, fast-paced environment  - Innovative team player with strong analytical, problem solving and planning skills.  - Strong organization skills and ability to effectively handle multiple concurrent assignments.  - Thorough understanding and compliance of database security best practices.  - Must be available for off-hour and on-call work in the event of outages, problems and off-hour required changes.  - Experience working in Agile Methodology  - Experience with Analysis Services(SSAS)  - Configure and monitor numerous MongoDB and NoSQL instances  - Automate routine tasks with your own scripts and open-source tools  - Solve production problems and participate in a 24x7 on-call rotation  - Improve database backups and test recoverability regularly  - Study the database needs of our applications and optimize them using MongoDB and NoSQL  - Maintain database performance and capacity planning  - Write documentation and collaborate with technical peers

Description: This is a Full Time position for a Business Intelligence Analyst II in Albany, NY Job Description: The Business Intelligence Analyst will implement solutions that support and drive qualitative and quantitative based decisions, facilitate business process and performance improvement, and support strategy development. They will evaluate process design, systems, workflow, system and process architecture, quality metrics, outcomes, and other environmental factors in order to adjust and optimize analytics and provide decision makers with actionable insights. The Business Intelligence Analyst will deliver reports and analytic applications that present high level performance indicators and allows for flexible exploration and drill down capabilities such that the root conditions driving the applicable performance indicator can be uncovered. The delivered reports and analytics will highlight and forecast costs, risks, and opportunities associated with new and changing business conditions. They will also respond to ad-hoc report requests across multiple business areas and will participate in the development of the Business Intelligence reporting tools. Mandatory Requirements: Minimum of an Associate's degree, preferably in a math, science, or technology related field of study. Bachelor's degree preferred.  Two to four years of experience.  Knowledgeable in system development lifecycle methods that support analyzing, developing, and maintaining complex data storage structures and data warehouse functions. Ability to manage and maintain data. Ability to communicate with business users to understand, document, and investigate data anomalies.  Ability to analyze data, monitor systems, identify problems, escalate problems according to procedure, recommend and implement solutions.  Capable of articulating technical matters to technical and non-technical counterparts in both information services and the business. Ability to support power users who develop reports on behalf of colleagues.  Ability to assist with the implementation, testing, troubleshooting, and maintenance of business intelligence tools. Ability to maintain and administer the corporate meta-data repository. Description: Job Description  Â    JPMorgan Chase & Co. (NYSE: JPM) is a leading global financial services firm with assets of $2.6 trillion and operations worldwide. The firm is a leader in investment banking, financial services for consumers and small business, commercial banking, financial transaction processing, and asset management. A component of the Dow Jones Industrial Average, JPMorgan Chase & Co. serves millions of consumers in the United States and many of the world's most prominent corporate, institutional and government clients under its J.P. Morgan and Chase brands. Information about JPMorgan Chase & Co. is available at www.jpmorganchase.com. Â About J.P. Morgan Corporate & Investment Bank J.P. Morgan's Corporate & Investment Bank is a global leader across banking, markets and investor services. The world's most important corporations, governments and institutions entrust us with their business in more than 100 countries. With $18 trillion of assets under custody and $393 billion in deposits, the Corporate & Investment Bank provides strategic advice, raises capital, manages risk and extends liquidity in markets around the world. About the team Credit Technology is focused on delivering best in class IT solutions to the Credit Trading business where JP Morgan is a market leader. We are a team of around 150 people with the core of our development effort based in the financial hubs of London, New York and Hong Kong where we partner closely with the quant research group and face off directly to the trading desks. Our core strength is providing technical expertise and software development skills that directly affect the ability of our business to generate revenue and remain the dominant player in the market. We are committed to hiring the brightest and best technical experts and in return can offer roles with direct trading and quant interaction on projects from electronic and algorithmic trading to grid based computation of real-time risk metrics. Â  About the role  We are looking to hire a software engineer to work in our Athena development team. Athena is the strategic risk, pricing, and trade management platform created at JP Morgan and is designed to enable rapid innovation. It is a Python based platform that offers Technologists, Quantitative Analysts and Risk Managers a cross-asset portfolio of models, frameworks and tools to use in building financial applications. Within Credit Technology, Athena is used extensively for Bond and CDS risk and analytics, whilst Reactive Athena (a realtime event processing framework) is used for algorithmic pricing and eTrading applications. The Athena development team is responsible for working with Trading and Quant Research to build out a range of components and core services focussed primarily on pricing, analytics, market making and real-time risk. The role will combine all aspects of software development from design and build to deployment, working within a team of experienced technologists. It requires an expertise in creating high quality and reusable components in a service-oriented architecture that will be leveraged by a variety of teams across Credit Technology as well as for direct deliveries to the desk. The successful candidate must be comfortable working as a front-office developer in a high pressure, challenging role with a focus on solving business problems via technology in a fast changing environment: time to market is critical, but without compromising on quality or performance. Align development with the overall Credit trading strategy. â€¢Â Â Â  Work across entire software development lifecycle â€“ requirements gathering, design, implementation, testing, deployment, handover to operate teams. â€¢Â Â Â  Work closely with the Quant team to develop pricing and analytic components in Python, leveraging the Athena platform â€¢Â Â Â  Enhance the team by demonstrating best practice throughout the software development lifecycle: testing, code review, accurate status reporting, focus on application resilience and â€œoperatabilityâ€ù. Knowledge/Experience â€¢Â Â  Â The ideal candidate will likely be qualified to degree level in Computer Science, Maths or related engineering discipline â€¢Â Â  Â Strong technology generalist â€“ experience building highly performant and resilient enterprise applications used within a high performance/realtime environment â€¢Â Â  Â Experience working in a team with a strong software development process (build, test, deploy etc)Â Â  Â  â€¢Â Â  Â Experience of developing in Python is preferred, but not necessary

Description: Please note that we can submit candidates who require sponsorship, but this client only allows TEKsystems to work with a select number of our approved partners.  Top Three Skills: Data profiling 2. Source to target Mappings 3. Data Modeling- Logical, Physical, Conceptual 4. Data visualization 5. SQL experience is also very important- We will be trying to use a tool called Informatica Data Quality to conduct data profiling. If for some reason we run into issues using this tool, we fall back to SQL. 6. LEADERSHIP and COMMUNICATION- This position is viewed as a Director-level role in the organization. Candidates need to be able to effectively and confidently describe and execute on Data Analysis/Modeling strategies for the program.  Job Description:A Lead data analyst performs a variety of tasks related to collecting, organizing and interpreting data. A data analyst will be responsible for inspecting, cleansing, transforming and modeling data. A data analyst will have to deal with uncertainty about data information completeness and quality. A data analyst will play a dominant role in business intelligence, advanced analytics, data integration and master data management efforts and will be involved with traditional application development projects where necessary. Role accountabilities A data analyst will have a natural inclination and passion toward problem solving in a disciplined process oriented fashion. A data analyst will - Critically evaluates information gathered from multiple sources, reconciles conflicts, classifies the information in logical categories  - Uses different visualization techniques and present the results of data exploration exercises - Understands the flow of data, business processes/technical interfaces that would be created or impacted - Documents the source to target mappings for both data integration as well as web services (consumer/provider mappings) that can be easily understood by the project team members with data quality and transformation rules - Identifies and documents sources of existing data as well as the new data. Understands use of master and reference data including sources and contributors. - Collaborates with data scientists and business partners and conducts data profiling and predictive analysis using a variety of standard tools - Creates conceptual, logical and physical data models and determines the most appropriate method to represent the data for business consumption. This includes all forms of physical representation of data, such as relational, dimensional, object, key-value (such as column families), and graph. Please note this list is not all inclusive. - Have joint accountability with data stewards and data architects on the projects to ensure conformance to enterprise data governance policies around information risk and data protection guidelines. Data analysts should be familiar with common policies around data masking and protection schemes. Recommended experiences  Data source identification, data profiling, interpretation of patterns and trends, assessment of and improvement of data quality, versatility with visualization tools and techniques to share analysis findings. Description: Production Data Analyst  The Production Data Analyst (DA) develops database queries, scripts, tools, and methods to manage data according to client requirements, within defined technical standards, and within time constraints. Emphasis is on ETL procedures. The DA is proficient with relational database concepts and practices, is able to evaluate and write complex SQL queries, and can create and maintain common database objects such as views, stored procedures, and user-defined functions. The DA should be familiar with and able to utilize code management and/or revision control tools and follow standard software development practices. The majority of time is spent developing and refining ETL processes, writing update queries, and writing ad-hoc queries on behalf of clients and stakeholders.Responsibilities of the Production Data Analyst     Develop and maintain ETL procedures according to client specifications and within defined technical standards.Develop and maintain database stored procedures, user-defined functions, views, triggers and other common database objects.Write custom and ad-hoc SQL queries and update queries.Follow prescribed software development standards, processes, procedures, methodologies, etc., according to departmental policies and conventions.Interact and correspond professionally with team members, project management, clients, and other stakeholders.Account for and accurately log time against project work.Qualifications of the Production Data Analyst     BS Computer Science or related discipline, or equivalent industry experience. 2+ years hands-on experience with MS SQL Server, 2008 R2 or higher, as a developer or DBA.Strong SQL skills, able to create and to evaluate complex SQL statements involving numerous tables and complex relationships.Ability to work in an environment with deadlines and shifting priorities.Basic understanding of and experience with query performance tuning.Experience developing and maintaining ETL procedures.Experience with SSIS preferred.Ability to communicate effectively, both verbally and in writing; able to adjust for intended audience. Fluency in English

Description: Job Description: Â  Job Title: Â  Data Scientist Location: Â  Portland, OR Reports To: Â  Statistical Research Management JOB FUNCTION The Data Scientist is part of the Statistical Operations and Data Science team that provides internal services to building and maintaining the data science methodologies comprising comScore's projection system for national television, local television, OnDemand, and digital viewership in a cross-platform measurement service. This position is expected to have a particularly significant role in comScore's measurement of Linear Television. In this role, the Data Scientist will work closely with other members of the Statistical Operations and Data Science team to work with large amounts of tune-level linear television data to build algorithms, tools, and custom projection solutions for precise cross-platform measurement using large-scale data sets in a fast-paced business environment. The Data Scientist will investigate and diagnose potential internally- and externally-facing issues, and design technology improvements to the projection system to improve the way that supports comScore leading cross-platform measurement products. This position will require working across other functional teams to meet the internal and external demands of the business. ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES o Independently identify appropriate data science techniques and projection methodologies that will be used to support comScore's cross-platform measurement products, and answer technical and business questions. o Build algorithms, tools, custom solutions, and new technologies from diverse and large-scale data sets to enhance comScore's measurement products, or contribute to new products. o Maintain existing algorithms, tools, solutions, and methodologies contributing to comScore's existing measurement products. o Build custom solutions to meet internal and client needs for cross-platform measurement. o Work closely with other functional teams, including Software Engineering, Product Management, Data Operations, Client Accounts Managers, and Sales Teams to develop and maintain the methodologies contributing to comScore's cross-platform measurement services. o Apply critical thinking to analyze process and data anomalies, field client inquiries, and diagnose problems and data issues. These tasks will include working with Software Engineers, Product Managers, Account Managers, Sales Managers, and Data Operations Analysts. o Summarize and visualize conclusions from large-scale data sets to support the decision making of internal business stakeholders using SAS, Excel, and other tools. o Communicate findings and results into measures of business impact. o Evaluate and confirm the integrity of large source data sets. o Be responsible for quality control and documentation of analysis and modeling to ensure on-time and accurate projection deliverables. o Manipulate, analyze, and validate large data sets using SAS and SQL analytical software, and extract quantitative and qualitative findings from large data sets. o Creatively solve tactical and strategic problems, bringing new approaches to management. o Ownership of routine tasks, ensuring all steps are completed within expected project deadlines with little supervision. QUALIFICATIONS o Requires a BA/BS in Statistics, Mathematics, or related field; Master's or Ph.D. degree preferred. o 2-4 years of relevant data science experience; comScore or other media measurement experience can be included. o Experience in building data science methodologies and custom data solutions for quantitative data measurement. o General familiarity with media industry and practices (theatrical, television, home entertainment, advertising, cross-platform, etc.); existing background in media, television, or cross-platform measurement services preferred. o Experience in data analysis and problem solving with large amounts of data; strong knowledge of SAS and SQL programming preferred. o Strong Excel skills. o Strong oral and written communication skills, including the ability to communicate findings to stakeholders and document project steps in detail. o Ability to work individually, as well as partner with small and large teams of other Data Scientists during all stages of projects, including planning and execution. o Ability to independently complete multiple simultaneous project tasks with little supervision. About comScore: Â  comScore (NASDAQ: SCOR) is the cross-platform measurement company that precisely measures audiences, brands and consumer behavior everywhere. comScore completed its merger with Rentrak Corporation in January 2016, to create the new model for a dynamic, cross-platform world. Built on precision and innovation, our unmatched data footprint combines proprietary digital, TV and movie intelligence with vast demographic details to quantify consumers' multiscreen behavior at massive scale. This approach helps media companies monetize their complete audiences and allows marketers to reach these audiences more effectively. With more than 3,200 clients and global footprint in more than 75 countries, comScore is delivering the future of measurement. For more information on comScore, please visit comscore.com. Description: Location Arlington, TX, US  Organization Name ITS, Database Engineering (01315)   Department Description   Brief Description  BASIC FUNCTION: Â   The ETL Developer II is responsible for extracting, transforming and loading (ETL) the data warehouse. The ETL Developer II will develop, maintain, and support the enterprise data warehouse system and corresponding data marts. This team member will analyze and review object and data models and the metadata repository in order to structure the data for better management and quicker access. The ETL Developer II will be competent to complete most data warehousing tasks independently, but may require some instruction and guidance on more complex tasks.  Detailed Description  JOB DUTIES: Â   * Execute data loading techniques for all data warehouse load projects which includes extracting a desired subset of data, transforming and converting data, creating mappings from source tables to destination tables, and writing and loading the result data into a target database table.  * Write SQL code to extract, transform, and load data ensuring compatibility with all tables and customer specifications.  * Facilitate and monitor data warehouse performance.  * Work with various levels of software developers to load data into the data warehouse and identify potential problem areas in the source system.  * Actively pursue and recommend areas of improvement for data loading techniques and/or population order.  * Work with internal business clients to problem solve data loading or integrity issues. Collaborate with the data modeling team to understand, interpret, and implement data warehouse requirements.  * Ensure metadata repository is accurate and updated regularly.  * Perform data load monitoring, analysis, and resolution.  * Make recommendations regarding problem resolution.  * Create, execute, and rearrange sessions; monitor load times of sessions; and rearrange processes to increase the efficiency and effectiveness of the loading process.  OTHER IMPORTANT DUTIES  * Ensure stability of source target application.  * Follow up with customers to ensure the data warehouse is meeting their specific demands in terms of analysis, content, presentation, and ease-of-use REPORTING RELATIONSHIP: Â  Reports to: Â  Data Warehouse Technologies Manager Direct Reports: Â  None  Job Requirements  QUALIFICATIONS: Â   Knowledge  * Working knowledge of Informatica, SQL, Oracle and/or similar tools.  * Demonstrated working knowledge in Data Warehouse loading, tuning and maintenance.  * Working knowledge of loading techniques for RDBMS.  Skills  * Demonstrated skills using Informatica or related tools, with an ability to write SQL database queries.  * Good oral and written communication skills.  * Advanced analytical skills.  * Ability to multi-task and organize projects.  * Ability to complete moderately complex data warehousing tasks independently.  Experience  * Bachelors degree in Information Systems, Computer Science or equivalent work experience required.  * Two to four years overall experience in Data Warehousing extracting, transforming and loading. WORK CONDITION: Â   Professional office environment. Position requires occasional overtime, travel, carrying a pager and nights.  Additional Details  JOB GRADE: Â  E.13

Position: Machine Learning and Signal Processing Research Engineer
Description: BAE Systems is looking for a Machine Learning and Signal Processing Research Engineer to join their Cognitive RF research group.  The cognitive RF group works on programs and problems that involve machine learning, optimization, detection & estimation, information theory, deep learning, and adaptive decision and control. These technologies are applied to a number of different RF domains, such as cognitive communications, radar, electronic warfare (EW), spectrum sensing, SIGINT, to name a few. The Cognitive RF research group is part of BAE Systems' Technology Solutions division which is heavily involved in advanced research concepts primarily from the various government research labs and organizations, including DARPA and IARPA.   Members of the group are involved in the entire cycle of research development, from the initial concept ideation and program shaping with potential customers and new business pursuits through the execution and transition of research concepts to BAE Systems' business areas and products.   Team members are typically involved in multiple simultaneous programs with roles including technical leadership, technical development, customer interaction, program management, or new concept development.   Most programs involve small teams of principal engineers and academically strong assistant researchers. This position can be based out of our Burlington, Massachusetts or Merrimack, New Hampshire facilities, though it will require collaboration with staff across our business areas and facilities in the northeast. Strong experience with mathematical model tools and languages; such as MATLAB, Python, etc. Experience in being part of a multi-disciplinary project team in research or development Strong and confident communication/presentation skills Eligible for a government security clearance (will be subject to a government security investigation). Current clearance preferred. The ideal candidate will have a MS in Electrical Engineering, Applied Math, Machine Learning, or similar field or 2 years of relevant demonstrated technical research. Strength in machine learning, signal processing, optimization detection & estimation, stochastic systems, applied statistics, and/or control Prior experience working with RF systems: radar, EW, comms, etc.
Skills: Machine Learning and Signal Processing Research Engineer
